Drain the @pineapple rings{1} (reserve the juice!) and chop into bite-sized pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces.

Halve the @baby corn{60%g} lengthways.

Trim the @spring onion{2} then finely slice.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @tomato ketchup{1}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @sweet chilli sauce{32%ml} and @pineapple juice{2%tbsp}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} or #wok{} on medium-high heat.

Add half the spring onion, the pepper, pineapple, baby corn and @sugar snap peas{150%g} and stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Pour the sauce you made in step 2 into the pan, stir and bubble until thick and glossy, ~{2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1%portion} according to pack instructions.

Stir half the @white sesame seeds{15} through the veggies then remove the #pan{} from the heat.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} with the sweet and sour veggies spooned over the top.

Finish with a scattering of the remaining spring onion and sesame seeds. Enjoy!